BENG 641: Advanced Nanotechnology in Health. 3 credits.
Presents interdisciplinary scientific and engineering approaches to solve relevant medical problems. Contents include polymer structure, composition, and material properties, natural and synthetic polymers, and their application to design novel nanocarriers for controlled drug release, scaffolds for tissue engineering, and new vectors for vaccines. The relevance of nanotechnology to advance treatments for cancer, infectious and neurodegenerative diseases are discussed in depth.  Offered by Bioengineering. May not be repeated for credit.
Recommended Prerequisite: BENG 541, or permission of instructor.
